                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="notes">
                    
                        <note n="1" xml:id="note-t-1">
                            

<p>Theo was depressed. <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_1633">Willem Laurens Kiehl</rs> – who, like Theo, boarded with <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_642 bio.xml#_643">the Rooses</rs> – had died on 22 September. <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_526">Mr van Gogh</rs> wrote to Theo on 25 September: ‘We are hard hit by the news of Kiehl’s death. I can imagine that you’re very conscious of it and feel it deeply. You lived with him for a fairly long time. How that Miss Roos will have taken care of him faithfully. Dying pathetically. So young. With a life behind him that was not easy, missing much of what others experience of love from their close relations’ (FR b2363).</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="2" xml:id="note-t-2">
                            

<p>Cf. Num. 20:17, Deut. 28:14 and Isa. 30:21.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
